course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
---

Bring 2 1/2 cups water and a large pinch of @salt{} to a boil in a #medium pot{}. Once boiling, add the @Basmati Rice{1%cup}. Cover and reduce to a low simmer for ~{15-20%minutes}, until tender. Keep covered until the rest of the meal is ready.

Wash and dry all produce. Trim and halve the @Green Beans{12%ounce}. Mince or grate the @Garlic{4%clove}. Peel and mince or grate the @Ginger{1%thumb}. Cut the @Scallions{4} whites and greens into 1-inch pieces. Core, seed, and thinly slice the @Red Bell Pepper{2}. Roughly chop the @Mint{1/2%ounce} leaves.

Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{4%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add the green beans, peppers, and scallions to the pan. Cook, tossing, for ~{4-5%minutes}, until tender and beginning to brown. Season with @salt{} and @Pepper{}. Remove from the pan and set aside.

Heat another large drizzle of oil in the same pan over medium heat. Add the garlic and ginger to the pan. Cook, tossing, for ~{1-2%minutes}, until fragrant. Season with salt and pepper.

Add the @Ground Pork{20%ounce} to the pan and increase heat to medium-high. Cook, breaking up the meat into pieces, for ~{4-5%minutes}, until browned. Toss the green beans, peppers, scallions, @Soy Sauce{12%teaspoon}, @Honey{2%tbsp} into the pan. Taste and season with salt and pepper, if necessary.

Serve: Remove pan from heat and toss in half the mint. Serve the Thai pork stir-fry on a bed of rice, garnish with the remaining mint, and enjoy!